<P>&gt; This is kinda nice, but it create a headache of calculations in
<BR>&gt; group PvP. In my Mud, players over a certain level, let's say 35
<BR>&gt; in EQ, will start to have no limit in PvP when fighting other
<BR>&gt; players above 35, they use the rationale that a lv35 player
<BR>&gt; should not be so easily killed with no chance of
<BR>&gt; retaliation(blicked) even by a high level player like lv50, and
<BR>&gt; players below 35 will be protected by a +/- lv limit. Not saying
<BR>&gt; I want this implemented but this is just one system out there
<BR>&gt; for you to see.
